        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-12-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="714" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d714">
                <head>No. 712.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Preston</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Hayti</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-12-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 3, 1888</date>. (Received December
                        4.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The undersigned, envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary of the Republic
                    of Hayti, has the honor to acknowledge the receipt of the note which the
                    honorable Secretary of State has addressed to him on <pb facs="1143" n="1007" xml:id="pg_1007"/> the 28th of November ultimo, on the subject of the affair
                    of the steamer <hi rend="italic">Haytian Republic.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>On the same date the undersigned, for his part, communicated to the Secretary of
                    State that he had received instructions from his Government relative to the same
                    affair.</p>
                <p>The undersigned hopes to be in a position to send to the Secretary of State, in a
                    very few days, his reply to the note of the 28th of the past month.</p>
                <p>The undersigned has the honor to renew to the Secretary of State the assurances
                    of his very high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stephen Preston.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
